It's not sufficient because it needs to loop and collect all outstanding zombies. E.g. with this version of zombie.c (also attached) it still waits:

#include <stdlib.h>
#include <unistd.h>

int main ()
{
        int i;

        for (i = 0; i < 10; i++)
                if (fork() == 0)
                        exit (0);
        sleep (1);
        return (0);
}
